The paper involves the use of computational intelligence to optimize the design of microbial fuel cell cascades, which suggests a strong connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of 3-D printing and the manipulation of hydrodynamics also suggests a connection to computer engineering (cs.CE) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the optimization of power output suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
